The Vice President expressed gratitude for the efforts being made to respond to Hurricane Michael and assured that the federal government is committed to helping affected areas recover. The U.S. Department of Agriculture will play a critical role in assisting the agricultural communities in Florida, Georgia, and the Carolinas. Emergency declarations have already been signed by President Trump for Florida and Georgia. The Vice President emphasized the government's commitment to providing resources and support for both urban and rural areas affected by the storm. He thanked the Secretary of Agriculture and the team of USDA employees for their efforts in assisting family farms impacted by the storm.